label.value: negative regulation of type II interferon production

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of interferon-gamma production. Interferon-gamma is also known as type II interferon.

label.value: positive regulation of type II interferon production

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of interferon-gamma production. Interferon-gamma is also known as type II interferon.

label.value: RNA biosynthetic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of RNA, ribonucleic acid, one of the two main type of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from ribonucleotides joined in 3',5'-phosphodiester linkage. Includes polymerization of ribonucleotide monomers. Refers not only to transcription but also to e.g. viral RNA replication.

definition.value: Note that, in some cases, viral RNA replication and viral transcription from RNA actually refer to the same process, but may be called differently depending on the focus of a specific research study.

label.value: bile acid secretion

value.value: The regulated release of bile acid, composed of any of a group of steroid carboxylic acids occurring in bile, by a cell or a tissue.

label.value: monocarboxylic acid metabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways involving monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (COOH) group or anion (COO-).

label.value: ribosome disassembly

value.value: The disaggregation of a ribosome into its constituent components; includes the dissociation of ribosomal subunits.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection cytoplasm

value.value: All of the contents of a plasma membrane bounded cell projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.

label.value: dendrite cytoplasm

value.value: All of the contents of a dendrite, excluding the surrounding plasma membrane.

label.value: response to insulin

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an insulin stimulus. Insulin is a polypeptide hormone produced by the islets of Langerhans of the pancreas in mammals, and by the homologous organs of other organisms.

label.value: cellular response to insulin stimulus

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an insulin stimulus. Insulin is a polypeptide hormone produced by the islets of Langerhans of the pancreas in mammals, and by the homologous organs of other organisms.

label.value: cellular response to hormone stimulus

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a hormone stimulus.

label.value: regulation of karyogamy

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of karyogamy, the creation of a single nucleus from multiple nuclei as a result of membrane fusion.

label.value: regulation of establishment or maintenance of cell polarity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the specification, formation or maintenance of anisotropic intracellular organization or cell growth patterns.

label.value: regulation of localization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any process in which a cell, a substance, or a cellular entity is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label.value: regulation of protein localization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label.value: regulation of polysaccharide metabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving polysaccharides.

label.value: regulation of polysaccharide biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of polysaccharides.

label.value: regulation of microtubule-based process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any cellular process that depends upon or alters the microtubule cytoskeleton.

label.value: regulation of organic acid transport

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of organic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label.value: negative regulation of organic acid transport

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of organic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label.value: positive regulation of organic acid transport

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of organic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label.value: secretion by cell

value.value: The controlled release of a substance by a cell.

label.value: secretion by tissue

value.value: The controlled release of a substance by a tissue.

label.value: mononuclear cell proliferation

value.value: The expansion of a mononuclear cell population by cell division. A mononuclear cell is a leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form.

label.value: regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

label.value: regulation of actin cytoskeleton organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

label.value: collagen metabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways involving collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

label.value: collagen biosynthetic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

label.value: regulation of collagen biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

label.value: negative regulation of collagen biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

label.value: positive regulation of collagen biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

label.value: regulation of actin filament-based process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any cellular process that depends upon or alters the actin cytoskeleton.

label.value: amino acid export across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of amino acids from inside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the extracellular region.
